RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 24000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIVINE FEMININE chased two wide near the back early, moved forward up the backstretch, advanced in the two path through the far turn, bid inside at the three-sixteenths pole, took over midstretch, cleared and began to drifted out with a furlong remaining and won going away. DR. TROUTMAN broke out to lose a step then rushed up outside inner pair to vie around the first turn, cleared to take full control in the middle stages, opened up on the far turn in the three path, challenged from both sides at the three-sixteenths pole, relinquished the lead to the winner soon after and outfinished VICENT'S SHADOW to hold second. VICENTE'S SHADOW settled inside at the back then angled out on the first turn, drew closer in the middle stages, chased four deep around the far turn, came five wide into the lane, launched a bid three deep at the three-sixteenths pole, could not stay with the winner in the furlong grounds and faltered late to lose the place. KRIXUS FLASH vied between rivals for command early, chased the leader past the five-eighths pole, went two wide into the far turn, moved out and exited that bend four wide, then weakened down the lane. PAPALE coaxed from the gate and vied inside a pair of runners around the first turn, chased past the five-eighths pole, lost ground while along the fence through the far turn and tired in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Divine Feminine
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2wide, bid inside 3/16, drifted out, clear

ENTRY.NAME: Dr. Troutman
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, vied 3deep, kicked clear, yielded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Cal-Bred or Cal-Sired horses Allowed a Three (3) Pound Weight Allowance.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCE OF MONACO hopped slightly to break a step slow, quickly went up to take the lead outside a pair of rivals, maintained command over inner pair through the turn, cleared under light coaxing at the top of the stretch and powered away without being asked for his best. LORD BULLINGDON also broke a step slow recovered quickly to challenge for the lead, vied between foes into and around the turn, could not go on with PRINCE OF MONACO at the top of the lane but kept on for a clear second. MASTERS SUNDAY chased the top trio in the two path into the turn, raced three wide into the drive, passed MALIBU RAIN for the show honors but failed to threaten. MALIBU RAIN showed early speed then vied inside a pair of runners for command, lost contact with outer rivals exiting the bend and tired in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Masters Sunday
ENTRY.OWNER: Net Birdie LLC Bartlett Charles and Egan Lyle

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Bullingdon
ENTRY.OWNER: Colbart Stables and Michael McCarthy Racing Stable Inc
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, vied between, no match

ENTRY.NAME: Prince of Monaco
ENTRY.OWNER: SF Racing LLC Starlight Racing Madaket Stables LLC Stonestreet Stables LLC Basho
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, vied 3deep, shook free, easily

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THINK OF ANITA raced up close four deep early, got bumped by JAYCEE while three deep into the turn, bid outside CAL around the bend, took over at the five-sixteenths pole, cleared inner rival then began to lug inward from the eighth pole to the sixteenth pole but still held safely in the end. CAL set the pace three deep early, angled to the inside around the bend, was overtaken at the five-sixteenths pole, fought to upper stretch then chased the winner through the final furlong. JAYCEE brushed inner rival leaving the gate, pressed between foes, drifted out and bumped THINK OF ANITA into the turn and had take up, entered the stretch four wide and was along for the show. AUNTIE BEV stumbled a bit and brushed with JAYCEE at the start, raced up close inside a trio of rivals up the backstretch, chased around the turn while moving out and came three wide into the lane, then weakened down the stretch. NOISEY BURGLAR reared as the gates opened and unseated the rider and walked off following the race. THERE WAS A PAIR OF INQUIRIES REGARDING RACE THREE. THE FIRST INVOLVED THE START OF NOISEY BURGLAR AND THE STEWARDS RULED THAT SHE CAUSED HER OWN PROBLEMS BY REARING AT THE START AND IS CONSIDERED A START. THE SECOND INQUIRY INVOLVED THE INCIDENT BETWEEN JAYCEE AND THINK OF ANITA ENTERING THE TURN. THE STEWARDS ACKNOWLEDGED THAT THINK OF ANITA DID SHIFT IN TO BOTHER JAYCEE AT THE SEVEN-SIXTEENTHS POLE BUT THE INCIDENT DID NOT WARRANT A DISQUALIFICATION.

ENTRY.NAME: Auntie Bev
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled bit/brushed, up close inside, 3wide into str, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Cal
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace 3deep, angled in turn, overtaken 5/16, clear 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Think of Anita
ENTRY.OWNER: Fessler Roger Paseta Baldo M and Spasiano Alexander J
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close 4deep, bumped 3deep 7/16, bid outside, lugged in str

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMOKEMONTHECLIFF cleared quickly, crossed over to the inside, moved out to come three wide into the lane, drifted in and out slightly in the lane and stayed clear under a drive. WARREN'S SHOW BIZZ dropped back early and was taken off the rail, went two wide into the turn, angled six wide into the lane, put in a mild late bid but could not reach the winner. SASSY TINKERBELL broke in and bumped rival, stalked outside a rival three wide into the turn, drew closer and loomed five wide into the lane but flattened in the final furlong. STELLA STARLIGHT took a bump from outside at the start, stalked two wide into the turn, eased further out and took aim four wide exiting the bend but weakened in the late stages. ROUND IN CIRCLES broke in, was forwardly placed early while racing to the inside of the pacesetter then had to alter out up the backstretch, came back to the inside entering the turn, exited the two wide and weakened. MIDNIGHT SUSI broke a step slow, raced four wide near the back into the turn, came six wide into the lane and failed to menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, angled 6wide into str, mild late bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 90. Starter Allowance Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROJECT LEADER sped to the front, showed the way two wide through the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and held safely under a drive. WINDING took a bump from outside at the start, chased along the rail then shifted to the two path at the three-eighths pole, moved back inside around the bend, steered off the fence in the lane and went willingly late to close the gap on the winner. LUCKY RYAN SEVEN was closest in pursuit three to four wide around the bend, saw the leader kick away in upper stretch and faltered to third. SHARP WARNING chased four wide outside rivals into the turn, moved into the three path around the bend, asked in the lane and failed to rally. J T'S WATCH chased outside a rival at the back early, went two wide into the turn, attempted to split foes early on the turn but lost his path when WINDING shifted out at the three-eighths pole, altered out into the clear and came four wide into the lane and failed to rally. PAUL VINCENTS POEM broke in and bumped rival, chased off the inside at the back, went tow wide into the turn, steered out and came five wide into the lane and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Winding
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, chased inside, moved out str, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: J T's Watch
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2wide, lost path 3/8, altered out, no rally

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: George Schmitt, Mary Clare Schmitt & Richard Meister

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASSUREDLY raced up close early then stalked three wide into the turn, four wide turning for home, closed well from the middle portion of the track and ran down AMAZING FLYER approaching the wire. AMAZING FLYER vied for command early then chased HEAVENLY KISSES leaving the backstretch, was closest in pursuit two then three wide around the turn, reeled in the leader approaching the eighth pole, took over shortly after and cleared briefly, then got run down by the winner in the final moments. SENT BY ANGELS raced outside a rival at the back early, advanced two wide through the turn, moved into striking distance in midstretch but got outkicked by the top pair. KIMBERLY'S DEVIL coaxed along early chasing off the rail, moved inside for the turn, came two wide into the stretch and passed tired rivals. OAK CREEK GAL was off a bit slow to begin, rushed up four deep to take over, cleared leaving the backstretch then crossed over, lugged out when asked left handed past the quarter pole, clung to a narrow lead with a furlong left to run and weakened once overtaken. HEAVENLY KISSES raced up close from inside early then chased the leader to the turn, saved ground around the bend and weakened in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Heavenly Kisses
ENTRY.OWNER: Ciaglia Racing LLC SAF Racing and Crusberg Harry A

ENTRY.NAME: Oak Creek Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow, rushed up, cleared, lugged out upper, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 100. Starter Allowance Purse 33000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HANDY DANDY showed early speed inside a pair of rivals into the first turn, moved into a stalking position up the backstretch, steered out around the far turn and bid four wide into the lane, got floated out by MASTERING before taking over in midstretch, then drew away in the furlong grounds. MASTERING was off slow and broke out then sent three deep into the turn, lost touch with the leader briefly then reengaged from outside up the backstretch, kept the pressure on through the far turn while in the three path, took over past the quarter pole and began to drift out, lost command midstretch and could not stay on with the winner in deep stretch. ATOMIC DROP took control early between rivals in the two path then cleared briefly leaving the clubhouse turn, pressured once again by MASTERING in the middle stages, dueled with that rival through the far turn, was overtaken past the quarter pole and weakened down the lane. EXPLAIN THIS AUDIT broke a step slow and was outkicked early while coaxed along, trailed along the rail into the first turn, moved off the inside into the backstretch, trailed two to three wide around the far turn and failed to menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALPINE THUNDER got bumped between rivals leaving the gate then crowded a bit between foes and took back early, trailed two wide into the turn, steered out and was five wide turning for home, closed steadily from the middle part of the track, drew alongside the top pair with a sixteenth remaining and drove past. DEVIL AMONG US vied for the lead three deep then chased two to three wide around the bend, moved out a bit into the lane then launched a bid at the top of the stretch, kept the pressure on into the final furlong, took over after crossing that marker and led with a sixteenth to go but got run down by the winner in the ned. AMERICAN CAT vied for the lead from inside then cleared rivals on the turn, showed the way off the inside into the drive, challenged by DEVIL AMONG US at the quarter pole, maintained a short lead to the eighth pole, lost command shortly after and stayed on well while getting outkicked by the top pair. SCARY FAST SMILE got bumped leaving the gate, stalked along the inside into the turn, cut the corner while ridden along into the lane, asked right and left handed in the drive but lacked a late bid. COWBOY CHARLIE broke through the gate and was reloaded, came away alertly then vied between rivals for command, could not keep up with the leader on the turn and began to drop back, then tired in the stretch run. STRAIGHTEN UP broke in and bumped inner rival, steadied when losing his path early, chased three then four wide around the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, stalked inside, no bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 5F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 23000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CITY OF CHAMPIONS stalked in the two path, loomed from outside into the lane, drew alongside the leader leaving the turn, gained the lead at the three-sixteenths pole, put away inner rival with a furlong to go and inched away. REIGN OVER ME was off a bit slow to begin, trailed on the inside into the turn, went two wide into the lane, rallied up the inside and got up for second. CAN'T RECALL tracked out of range two wide into the turn, angled out into the lane, summoned a mild rally but got outkicked for the place honors. BLACK MAGICIAN sent for the front and took control set the pace on the inside around the turn, challenged entering the stretch, relinquished the lead in upper stretch and flattened to fourth. LAMPY stalked three wide into the turn, came four wide into the lane, drifted in and out in the lane and lacked a bid. ABERDEEN'S KNIGHT sat off the pace four wide into the turn, exited the bend five wide and failed to threaten. MEDINA MAN chased five wide off the pace into the turn, moved into the four path around the bend and failed to menace. BOOMER JUSTICE broke a step slow, raced up close on the inside early, chased two wide into the lane, got hemmed in at the three-sixteenths pole and weakened. MONGOLIAN MASTER raced near the back four wide into the turn, trailed five wide into the drive and came up empty.

ENTRY.NAME: Boomer Justice
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, up close inside, 2wide, hemmed in 3/16, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: City of Champions
ENTRY.OWNER: Howard and Janet Siegel Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Reign Over Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow, inside-2wide, rallied, up for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Lampy

BARELY FUNTIONAL chased at the back early, traveled three wide into the turn, tipped four wide into the stretch, drifted inward in the lane and finished willingly to whittle the gap on the winner while gaining second.
